<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="84">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Diﬀers">Diﬀers</normalizedToken>
from other 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Haploporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Haploporus" order="Polyporales" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Haploporus</taxonomicName>
species by its relatively large pores, 2-3 per mm, a dimitic hyphal structure with non-dextrinoid skeletal hyphae, the absence of dendrohyphidia, and wide oblong basidiospores measuring 12-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
